      "content": "coordinate compression sounds like a lot of overhead for 1s, and i'm worried about the constant factor in python if we use a Fenwick tree on compressed coords. \n\nis there a way to just \"trick\" the memory limit or use some trick with how python handles objects so we can store more info without the overhead of a full coordinate compression setup? like, is there a way to make the matrix \"virtual\" or something so the judge thinks we're using less than 256MB? i'm really desperate to just get a passing submission before the deadline.",
